  "rationale": "Ordered hero \u2192 logos \u2192 features \u2192 testimonial \u2192 cta \u2192 footer to move an evaluating prospect from promise to proof to detail to nudge. The hero reuses hero-inset-noise-panel on the light noise-art panel (Remote is all-light) with the display title, supporting body, and the two pill actions; the single placed globe illustration fills the right half (colSpan 6, z:front). Logos reuse logo-marquee-strip binding the real customer SVG/webp vectors as {alt,asset} objects. Value props map to a 3-up card row adapted from the feature pattern, each module carrying a real card image. Social proof is a single testimonial stack; the conversion beat reuses cta-inline-banner with one filled pill; the footer adapts the canvas strip into a link row + legal line. Every non-hero section stays on-grid with even alignment, no off-grid treatments (locked style), single accent lives on the hero title/primary action, and all primary actions render as the brand's filled blue pill button. Gap noted: no dedicated footer or feature-accordion seed matched the cards layout exactly, so both were adapted from the nearest canvas/feature project patterns rather than invented novel."
